title: * Re: 4.0GeV looks geat to TDUND. Openning TDUND gets...
text: Set BYDSH lower MPS limit to 18% instead of 5% for the purposes of BBA. The real issue here (thanks Jeremy for making this clear) is that the MPS can only do a linear fit to the energy vs. magnet current, whereas magnet software uses a polynomial (N=7 or so). Cannot make these align over the entire range. 4.0Gev is the bottom end of that which we never use except for BBA. Add to the CATER to put the 5% lower threshold back after BBA.

He's about to start "processing" it (meaning conditioning the caps, not running RF). 10-4 hasn't been worked on yet but wasn't touched during the shutdown so should be good to go. Critt will try turning it on to confirm that it still works okay.

title: 10-2: PFN Conditioning/Tuning CATER 154510
text: After confirming with ACR, triggers were provided to power up the station and check the PFN. At first, turn on would produce an immediate ACOC fault. Troubleshooting revealed that the ACOC trip point on the HV regulator board had dropped to .18V (should be 2V). Reason for that unknown. Able to readjust the trip point to get the station on. Started at 5kV, slowly raising HV 1kV every couple of minutes; then 2kV increments starting at 10kV. At 16kV, PFN definitely needed to be tuned. Tried cold tuning to no avail. Needs to be hot-tuned. Got HV back to set point (19.33kV). Put station in remote for ACR to start RF processing. Informed them of the tuning issue. ct

title: 10-3: PFN Conditioning/Tuning CATER 154511
text: After confirming with ACR, triggers were provided to power up the station and check the PFN. As soon as station was made ready, SCRTD went out. Replaced unit: PCD06910 out, PCD03227 in, DEPOT updated. Started at 5kV, slowly raising HV 1kV every couple of minutes; then 2kV increments starting at 10kV. At 16kV, PFN definitely needed to be tuned. Did not try to cold tune (PFN looks the same as 10-2). Needs to be hot-tuned. Got HV back to set point (21.95kV). Put station in remote for ACR to start RF processing. Informed them of the tuning issue. ct
